<dl id="n26263l"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n26" href="#n26263l">N26 (VI.B.18)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n26all.htm#n26263l"> 263(l)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> pupillarity</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[The Law of the Family Relations]</font>&mdash;<font size="-1">GENTILE GUARDIANSHIP</font>&mdash;So long as Rome was patrician the <i>gens</i> apparently charged itself with the guardianship of a clansman&apos;s orphan pupil children and his widow and unmarried daughters above <mark>pupillarity</mark> after his decease (<i>tutela</i>) <small> &ldquo;ROMAN LAW&rdquo; <a name="EBRL2" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EBRL2"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 540</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
